        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: hoist timer declaration to avoid TDZ ReferenceError in abortable delay",
        "body": "Related: #98464\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes a latent TDZ bug where `finish()` references `timer` declared as `const` after `finish` was defined, risking `ReferenceError` if abort fires before timer assignment.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nHoist `timer` as `let` above `finish` so it is safely `undefined` when `finish` fires early.\n\n## User Impact\n\nNo user-visible change. Removes fragile declaration-order dependency.\n\n## Evidence\n\nRuntime verification (fix/tdz-feishu-async, rebased on upstream/main 6495358f):\n\n```\nasync.test.ts — Test Files 1 passed, Tests 5 passed\n✓ waitForAbortableDelay > resolves false immediately when already aborted\n✓ waitForAbortableDelay > resolves true after the full delay when not aborted\n... (5/5 ✓, Duration 401ms)\n```\n\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard. All abort paths verified, no ReferenceError.",
